15 SECTION 4. A new section to chapter 37-15 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
16 and enacted as follows:
17 Meals provided to employees of the veterans' home.
18 In the event of a disruption of operations, the veterans' home may provide meals at a fair
19 value or without a charge to employees of the veterans' home as required by the job
20 assignments of the employees.
21 SECTION 5. EXEMPTION - LINE ITEM TRANSFERS - REPORT. Notwithstanding section
22 54-16-04, the director of the office of management and budget may transfer up to $400,000
23 from special funds from the salaries and wages line item to the operating expenses line item in
24 section 1 of chapter 7 of the 2023 Session Laws, during the period beginning with the effective
25 date of this Act, and ending June 30, 2025, as requested by the veterans' home. The veterans'
26 home shall notify the legislative council of any transfers made pursuant to this section.
27 SECTION 6. LEGISLATIVE MANAGEMENT STUDY - VETERANS' HOME FACILITIES.
28 During the 2025-26 interim, the legislative management shall consider studying the usage of the
29 veterans' home facilities. The study must consider any organizational changes necessary to
30 increase resident census at the veterans' home, potential uses for unoccupied space, and
31 federal requirements. The legislative management shall report its findings and
